# Air-Audit Pipeline API — restart `npm run dev` after any change here.
# OpenAPI: https://nocturnal-cloistered-mamie.ngrok-free.dev/docs
#
# Client polls via same-origin proxy: /api/air-audit/* → your backend (no ngrok HTML in the browser).

# Option A — typical dev (URL is baked into the client bundle at dev start):
NEXT_PUBLIC_AIR_AUDIT_API_BASE=https://nocturnal-cloistered-mamie.ngrok-free.dev

# Option B — optional extra flag (use if you rely on server-only AIR_AUDIT_API_BASE):
# AIR_AUDIT_API_BASE=https://nocturnal-cloistered-mamie.ngrok-free.dev
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ENABLE_AIR_AUDIT=1

# Optional bearer when the API enforces auth:
# AIR_AUDIT_API_TOKEN=
# NEXT_PUBLIC_AIR_AUDIT_API_TOKEN=

# App entry: WebGL “AeroOps” splash runs on every refresh by default, then the dashboard.
# To open straight into the dashboard (no splash):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SKIP_SHADER_INTRO=1

# Google Gemini (server-only — never use NEXT_PUBLIC_ for API keys)
# Get a key: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=
# Optional: pin one model id. If unset, /api/ai/chat tries several (2.5-flash → 2.0 → 1.5 variants).
# List: https://ai.google.dev/gemini-api/docs/models
# GEMINI_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# Optional: pre-filled recipient for the green “Contact” button on findings (maintenance / work orders).
# NEXT_PUBLIC_MAINTENANCE_CONTACT_EMAIL=ops@yourcompany.com
